docs.snippet: HEIBERGER--Edwin, A prominent Long Island-based real estate developer and lifelong entrepreneur who led the construction of a notable series of luxury custom homes throughout parts of Suffolk County, including the Hamptons, and along Nassau County...
docs.lead_paragraph: HEIBERGER--Edwin, A prominent Long Island-based real estate developer and lifelong entrepreneur who led the construction of a notable series of luxury custom homes throughout parts of Suffolk County, including the Hamptons, and along Nassau County's Gold Coast, and founded a prestigious racquet and yacht club in the area, died Tuesday in Commack. He was 74. A go-getter and man of many ideas, Heiberger began his first business, Turf Sprinklers, an underground lawn sprinkler company, in his late teens, operating as a pioneer in that industry for 10 years throughout his days as a high school football star and student at the University of Oklahoma. Following the sale of the sprinkler business, Heiberger opened the prominent Harbour Point Racquet and Yacht Club in Freeport, Nassau County, which he sold in 1982. A love for real estate led him to start his own luxury custom home-building project that same year, in which he oversaw the development of several ground-up residential properties, including a 24-home subdivision in East Quogue. Heiberger quickly established himself as a known and reputable builder across Nassau and Suffolk Counties, and remained in the business until recently. Edwin Heiberger was born on October 23, 1938, in Brooklyn, the son of William, a prominent New York attorney, and Irene. He was reared in Far Rockaway, Queens, where he met his high school sweetheart and wife of 53 years, Sidnie, before relocating with her to Baldwin, NY, and then on to Dix Hills in Suffolk County, where the two spent the remainder of their adult lives. A mentor and role model to friends, employees and above all, his family, Heiberger is survived by his wife Sidnie; his children Lisa, Steven and Andrew; his six grandchildren, Ashley, Alex, Samantha, Madison, Lucas and Nikki; and sisters Meta and Holly.
